          "description": "The Kansas City Cardiomyopathy Questionnaire contains 12 items that measure the effect of heart failure on health and quality of life. Total scores are scaled from 0 to 100 and frequently summarized in 25-point ranges, where scores represent health status as follows: 0 to 24: very poor to poor; 25 to 49: poor to fair; 50 to 74: fair to good; and 75 to 100: good to excellent",
          "timeFrame": "4 weeks"
        }
      ],
